{"overview":"This D minor piece exhibits a brooding, balladic character built on a ternary-like arch (A–B–A''–Coda) whose most distinctive feature is a bold modal mixture shift to D major for the stormy middle section, framed by pervasive flat-side harmonies (bVI, bVII, iv) that saturate the outer sections with dark, modal color and chromatic inner-voice tension throughout.","cross_piece_tags":["ballade","ternary","modal_mixture","chromatic_mediant","lyrical","tragic","dramatic","melancholic"]}
